        <div class="bg-white p-3 rounded mb-3">
            <p>Rui, I appreciate your insightful response. I agree that there are varying degrees of failure consequences and approaches to determining the need for spare parts. Conducting quantitative analysis, as you mentioned in your post, is crucial in such situations. This concept resonated with me when I made my previous post, and you articulated it effectively here. Your work on the cooling water tower serves as a valuable contribution to making a strong business case for investing $40,000 in a critical spare part. When making such decisions, I must compete for funding against other departments with equally convincing proposals for alternative uses of the capital.</p>
